	   <a name=99919864538894></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99919864538894><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99919864538894>My point of view</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99919864538894#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 30th 3:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personnaly love my mage.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is an awesome class.  I have been able to explore many many dungeons solo and have had a blast with the various item summoning spells.  I am looking forward to the new item spell from SoL.  About the only grip I have with the magician class would be the lack of varity in the damaging spells.  Basically it boils down to fire or magic based spells.  As "elementalists"  I think a better mix would have been fire and cold based spells.  Notice I dropped the magic based spell.  In my opinion this falls more in line with the Wizard class. (I'm giving a concession for the gain of cold based here)  As for the lack of root, well yes it would be nice but I have never found it to be an utter stop gap.  Work around this by using the earth pet.  I would say that I play solo 75% of the time and I am now almost 54th level.  My pets are amazing and I get many an awe from other players on their abilities.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
