	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your advice isn't bad but there are some things I would like to add.&nbsp;&nbsp;Going to the Wisp Island I think its called Kerra, (its the place with the cat people) is a REALLY bad idea if youre a level 8-10 mage.  There are no guards, and no zone.  This is important for a couple of reasons.  First is the Island Madmen, they are KOS spell casters and consistently under-con.  Second is the multiple wisp issue.  You can attack a wisp and have a second or third roll up on you before you finish the first.  If you are in this situation there and your pet eats it, more than likely so will you. I wasnt really surprised by the number of wisps, as much as the lack of Greater Light Stones.  After more than 2 and a half hours; 3 gates, 3 deaths, and 7 pets I got one stone  :(<br>Im a level 11 mage, with a decent dagger an AC 8 robe and miscellaneous other gear (no real twinkage goin on here).  <br>  Im kind of bummed because I made the trek from Freeport to go here.  The hike from Qeynos to NK is a HUMP! even with SOW.  So in my opinion hunting wisps here is not really worthwhile.  For levels 7-11 (cant say beyond 11  :P  )  I would stick to East commons and West commons hunting large/Giant Spiders for spider silks.  They tend to sell for 1pp a piece and you can get up to 4 from one spider.  Stick reasonably close to the Zone line especially in W commons and you ought to be alright.  I raised more than enough PP this way but Larges are conning green and Giants are probably low blue to me now so off to wisp Island I went. Many of the Wisps are conning blue to me now so Its hard to figure those same blue wisps will con anything but green in a couple of levels.<br><br>This post is my preliminary observation on the Kerra Isle portion of Tims guide.  Im going to give it a little more effort and advise if my opinion changes.  If the GLS'don't drop more often I guess I'll move on the Stonebrunt Ive heard that good for 12-20 if you can group?<br><br>Thanks for reading  :)<br>***********************Amayarick, lvl11 mage<br>***************************************Saryrn<br><br><br>   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
