	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok im almost to 20 and since you get specialization at 20 this is how it was explained to me.<br><br>When you reach 20 not only will you have regular mage skills like abjuration, conj, div, evok, etc meter (ie if u cast invisi on yourself enought times youll see a msg that says "You have become better at div (98)"<br><br>Well when you hit 20 you will have a specialization skill gauge for example if you cast ivisi on yourself enought times you will see not only<br><br>"you have become better at div (99)"<br><br>but you will see the specialization skill of that certain skill rise<br><br>"you have become better at specialize div (1)"<br><br>now i dont know if the spec msg above is absolutely correct but that is what was explained to me.<br><br>Now specialization is a race.&nbsp;&nbsp;Whichever spec skill (div, evok, conj, etc) gets to 50 first is the only ONE that can go above 50 and is your SPECIALIZED skill all the rest stay at 50.  I myslef and going to max out Evocation to 50 first so I can go about 50 on that because thats the skill you use to do most of your Damage (Direct and Area) spells.<br><br>Specialization itself helps reduce mana cost and lessens fizzles and mabye even casting and rec time not exactly sure yet.  Hope this helps and hope I got the explanation os spec correct.<br><br>Seriallova<br>lvl 19 Mage<br>Erollisi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
