	   <tr><td colspan=2>Mages are not underpowered, they merely lack group friendly spells and many groups are afraid of the inherent risk of using pets because so many mages suck at pet control.<br><br>Mages can deal damage faster than any other class in the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;This comes at a fairly significant price but we seem to pay most of that price between levels 20-38.  After 39 things only get better as pet power goes up exponentially.<br><br>While root or snare or especially fear would be great, my answer is to get jboots.  I think jboots increase a mages power more so than any other class because they lessen our major weakness (mob control) and allow pet kiting.<br><br>Earth pets are fairly useless and mages only depend on them because they do not understand how to correctly use their DDs and balance mob aggro.  I did  not use an earth pet for about 40 levels until lvl 51.  The lvl 51 earth pet root spell actually does work pretty well on blues.  But after having learned to live without root for 50 levels I find it more of an annoyance than a help.  It prevents me from pet kiting and severely lowers the damage output from the 51 pet because it is rooting all the time.  The 51 pet also costs 100mana more then the 49 pets and does not seem 100mana better, especially if you chain summon a lot.<br><br>At 49 I could easily solo 2 blues simultaneously in CoM.  While mages may not be wanted much in groups, how many other classes can do that?<br><br>Just look forward to Anti-summon shield at lvl 60 once SoL comes out.<br><br>If you already suck at controlling your pet, get aggroed on in groups frequently when nuking, and rely on earth pets to survive soloing, do the rest of us a favor and chose a new class.  The mages greastest deficiency is the poor reputation we have been given because our class is difficult to play well and played so poorly by so many inept mages out there.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
