	   <tr><td colspan=2>im a lvl 23 Human Enchanter, and my friend, who is going to be my apprentice in game, asked me the very same question: "what would u recommend for logical equipment?" she said...<br>my answer is this:<br>if u want the best u can get NOW, look into the quests in Ak'Anon first. some will give u pretty decent items; (especially the metal bits one for the Glow Rod...i think that's what it is)<br>short of that, save up for cured silk, or some type of cloth armour. u should b able to lvl up 2 a minimum of 7 b4 u even step foot into steamfront. but once u do, try to get a port over to Erudin, and get the Servant's Staff (quest) it has the same stats as a regular staff, but has +5 mana (or hitpoints. cant remember) and if i remember the quest correctly, it can be equipped in your secondary melee slot. if that's true, put it there, and get a regular staff, and just milk the plus u get from it. then, go to qeynos, do the tacklebox quest, and get the tacklebox. (free 10-slot container) do the tax collection quest, and get a brass ring, then get the tax collection box again. (10-slot container) go to the paladin guild, and get a container from one of thier quests. (dont remember which one.)<br>once u get all of these, go kill one of the fish in the temple of life, and turn in the LORE/NO DROP fish to the guy in the pool. (he WILL kill u once, but that's ok. u can get the faction back.) turning in the fish will get u a +3INT ring!<br><br>the point is, look into some low-lvl quests from ALL the starting cities, and see what a gnome magician could accomplish at your lvl...<br>ok?<br>good luck!!!<br><br><br><br>Laquisis Lorekyper<br>LVL 23 Human Enchanter<br>Aegis of Justice<br>Povar<br><br>"dont underestimate my power!"<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
